<FILE path="OS/userland/terminal.c">updated</FILE>
<FILE path="OS/userland/include/zenith/user.h">updated: Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA=5</FILE>
<FILE path="OS/userland/session.c">updated: bridge command handling + terminal tab forwarding</FILE>
<SYSCALL>none new</SYSCALL>
<VERIFY>
VC-1a: PARTIAL - command table contains HELP SYSINFO ECHO CLEAR DESKTOP REBOOT ENV EXPORT ALIAS HISTORY WHOAMI PWD CD LS CAT EXIT SETTINGS OVERVIEW PKG_INSTALL PKG_REMOVE PKG_UPDATE PKG_SEARCH PKG_LIST PKG_INFO. Build verification passed. Interactive valid/invalid execution not fully automated.
VC-1b: PASS - tab completion implemented against command table in complete_command(); session forwards Tab to focused terminal instead of stealing it for focus switching.
VC-1c: PASS - pack_args() packs argv[1..] into a single string for execute_external(); z_spawn(path,arg) ABI unchanged.
VC-1d: PASS - static allocation only; no malloc/calloc/realloc/free symbols; no heap use added.
VC-1e: PASS - every command has CLASS_NATIVE or CLASS_BRIDGE_ONLY. Bridge handler calls send_bridge_command(); no z_open/z_read/z_close in bridge path. Only CAT native handler calls z_open/z_read/z_close.
VC-1f: PASS - argv[0] normalized with to_upper()/uppercase_text() during tokenize(); PKG_* args lowercased in send_bridge_command() before Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA forwarding.
VC-1g: PASS - history is now persisted outside the terminal process in the session service via existing Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA IPC. Terminal startup sends BRG HIST_LOAD; command commit sends BRG HIST_PUSH <line>; session replies to the terminal with HIST <line>. This survives terminal process restart while respecting read-only initramfs and adding no storage syscall.
Binary size: 16026/32768 bytes.
</VERIFY>
