Build: mingw32-make all -> PASS.
Binary: OS/build/userland/terminal.bin = 16026 bytes.
Include audit: terminal.c includes only zenith/user.h and stdbool.h; user.h includes stdint.h.
Forbidden symbols: no malloc, printf, string.h, stdio.h, stdlib.h.
Bridge-only z_open/z_read/z_close audit: no calls in send_bridge_command() or handle_bridge(); CAT is native and owns the only z_open/z_read/z_close calls.
History persistence: terminal sends BRG HIST_PUSH and BRG HIST_LOAD over Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA; session stores 8 commands in session_state and replies directly to terminal target with HIST frames. No new syscall, no writable initramfs mutation.
</EVIDENCE>
<SUMMARY>
Phase 1 implementation compiles and is under cap. Gate status: PASS using session-backed history persistence over the existing UI IPC bridge.
</SUMMARY>
